.TH BUDGE 1 "June 2026" "budge 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
budge \- self-hosted household budgeting glue around hledger, SimpleFIN, and Paisa
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B budge
.RI [ \-\-dry\-run ]
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B budge
automates a plain-text accounting stack: it pulls bank transactions daily
through SimpleFIN, imports them with stock hledger CSV rules, asks an AI to
suggest categories for whatever the rules miss, holds those suggestions in a
reviewable pending state that still counts against the budget, and provides a
fast vendor-grouped weekly review.
All data lives as ordinary hledger journal files in a git repository.
.PP
.B budge
is orchestration only.
It deliberately wraps none of hledger's own functionality \(em there is no
.B budge balance
and no
.BR "budge report" .
Reporting, queries, and validation are plain hledger commands run against the
journal, for example:
.PP
.nf
    hledger \-f main.journal balance \-\-budget \-M expenses
    hledger \-f main.journal register assets:transfers
    hledger \-f main.journal check
.fi
.PP
A transaction's category is decided at import but only trusted at promote:
rule-matched transactions enter the books cleared
.RB ( * ),
AI-suggested ones wait in
.I pending.journal
with status
.B !
until the operator reviews and promotes them.
Every correction made during review becomes a permanent rule, so the AI's
share of the work shrinks over time.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B setup
Interactive, idempotent bootstrap.
Verifies prerequisites, exchanges the one-time SimpleFIN setup token for a
permanent access URL (stored only in
.IR secrets.env ),
maps bank accounts to hledger account names, scaffolds the data repository,
seeds transfer/payment rules, backfills 90 days of history with computed
opening balances and balance assertions, installs the systemd timers, writes
the Paisa dashboard configuration, and hands off to the budget wizard.
Safe to re-run at any point; existing values are kept when you press Enter.
.TP
.B fetch \fR[\fB\-\-backfill\fR \fIDAYS\fR]
Pull new transactions from SimpleFIN, append them to the immutable raw CSVs
under
.IR import/raw/ ,
import rule matches into
.I main.journal
as cleared, queue the rest in
.IR pending.journal ,
append a balance assertion per account, and commit.
Duplicates are impossible: every transaction ID is recorded in
.I import/state/
and checked against the journals.
With
.B \-\-backfill
also writes opening balance entries against
.IR equity:opening-balances .
.TP
.B categorize
Send uncategorized pending transactions to the configured AI provider and
write its suggestions (category, confidence, one-line rationale) into
.IR pending.journal .
The request contains only payee/description, amount, date, and source account
name \(em never account numbers, balances, or history.
Every decision is appended to
.I ai/ai-decisions.log
before it is used.
Malformed model output is rejected; the transaction stays
.I expenses:uncategorized
rather than guessed at.
The categorizer's entire write surface is pending.journal and the log.
.TP
.B review \fR[\fB\-\-edit\fR]
Weekly vendor-grouped review of pending transactions, largest groups first.
Per group: approve, correct the vendor (writes a rule, then regenerates
pending so every matching transaction updates at once and the vendor never
returns), or correct a single transaction (one-off, no rule).
.B \-\-edit
opens
.I pending.journal
in
.BR $EDITOR .
Ends by offering promote.
.TP
.B promote
The explicit final step:
.B hledger check
is a hard gate (any failure stops everything with nothing written, committed,
or pushed), then pending entries are flipped to cleared, appended to
.IR main.journal ,
pending is truncated, review outcomes are appended to the decision log, and
one commit captures journal and rules changes together, followed by a push.
.TP
.B plan \fR[\fB\-\-bootstrap\fR|\fB\-\-reassess\fR] [\fB\-\-months\fR \fIN\fR]
Budget planning wizard.
Asks exactly three questions (monthly take-home, savings target, and what
you're saving for / what's changing) and stores them in
.IR household.md .
Bootstrap mode analyzes your real imported spending and proposes three
confirmable artifacts: a chart of accounts, monthly envelope amounts
constrained by income minus savings, and 20\(en30 starter merchant rules.
Re-assessment mode reports variance per category with streaks and dormancy
over the trailing
.I N
months (default 3) and proposes a budget diff for approval.
Nothing is written without explicit confirmation, and the wizard cites only
your own numbers \(em no external benchmarks.
.TP
.B regenerate
Rebuild
.I pending.journal
from the raw CSVs, the current rules, and the decision log.
Pending is a derived artifact; this is always safe.
Entries that now match a rule move to
.I main.journal
as cleared; operator one-off corrections are preserved.
.TP
.B push
Push the data repository to its git remote.
.TP
.B cheatsheet \fR[\fItopic\fR]
Print curated hledger recipes for common questions (find transactions by
vendor/category/amount, monthly statements, budget views, pending-only
filters). Prints commands only — budge never runs reports for you. An
optional topic word filters the list, e.g.
.BR "budge cheatsheet month" .
.TP
.B notify \fR[\fB\-\-unit\fR \fIUNIT\fR] [\fB\-\-review\-nudge\fR]
Outbound notifications (used by the systemd units).
.B \-\-unit
sends the failed unit's name, exit status, and last ~20 journal lines to the
configured webhook;
.B \-\-review\-nudge
sends \(lqreview ready \(em N transactions pending\(rq.
This path only sends data out; nothing can write back through it.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Print every intended action and write nothing: no files, no commits, no
pushes, no AI calls.
Accepted by every command.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/budge/budge.conf
Machine-local settings (INI): data repo path, AI provider/endpoint/model,
sync schedules, notification webhook, review day.
.TP
.I ~/.config/budge/secrets.env
Secrets, mode 600, outside the data repo:
.B SIMPLEFIN_ACCESS_URL
and
.BR AI_API_KEY .
.TP
.I <repo>/main.journal
The source of truth.
Includes
.IR accounts.journal ,
.IR budget.journal ,
and
.IR pending.journal .
.TP
.I <repo>/import/rules/*.rules
Stock hledger CSV rules, one file per bank account.
Vendor rules accumulate here; transfer/payment patterns stay last so they
take precedence.
.TP
.I <repo>/import/raw/YYYY-MM/*.csv
Immutable record of what SimpleFIN returned, committed to git.
.TP
.I <repo>/ai/agent.md
The categorizer's instructions.
Operator-editable; the live category list and recent approved examples are
substituted in at run time.
.TP
.I <repo>/ai/ai-decisions.log
Append-only JSON-lines audit log of every AI suggestion, rejection, manual
override, and review outcome.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B BUDGE_CONFIG_DIR
Alternate configuration directory (default
.IR ~/.config/budge ).
.TP
.B BUDGE_REPO
Alternate data repository path, overriding budge.conf.
.TP
.B BUDGE_HLEDGER
Alternate hledger binary.
.TP
.B EDITOR
Used by
.B budge review \-\-edit
and the wizard's edit steps.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success, non-zero on any failure.
Failures in timer-driven runs trigger the systemd
.B OnFailure
notification path.
.SH EXAMPLES
First-time setup, then a manual pull and review:
.PP
.nf
    sudo ./setup.sh
    budge fetch
    budge review
.fi
.PP
See what a fetch would do without touching anything:
.PP
.nf
    budge \-\-dry\-run fetch
.fi
.PP
Re-assess the budget over the last six months:
.PP
.nf
    budge plan \-\-reassess \-\-months 6
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR hledger (1),
.BR systemd.timer (5),
.BR git (1)
.PP
SimpleFIN protocol:
.UR https://www.simplefin.org/protocol.html
.UE .
Paisa dashboard:
.UR https://paisa.fyi
.UE .
.SH NOTES
The data repository contains your complete financial history in plain text.
Keep its git remote
.BR private .
